
1. Sierra Leone, on the Atlantic Ocean in West Africa, is half the size of Illinois.
2. The Bulom people were thought to have been the earliest inhabitants of Sierra Leone,
 followed by the Mende and Temne peoples in the 15th century and thereafter the Fulani.
3. The Portuguese were the first Europeans to explore the land and gave Sierra Leone its name.
4. Four languages: English (official), Mende (southern vernacular), Temne (northern vernacular), 
Krio (lingua franca).
5. Mangrove swamps lie along the coast, with wooded hills and a plateau in the interior. 
The eastern region is mountainous.
6.